<br>
Your friends is right that the baseline of good aggro is a low delay weapon in your main hand, and a good ratio weapon in your offhand. (<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>often this means slower but more damaging, although not always</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->)<br>
<br>
This general guideline will only serve you for so long however, in the mid 50's other classes come into their full power and fast efficient weapons will no longer hold aggro by themselves. It is at this point in your warrior career that procs become a very important concern. <br>
<br>
The procs of weapons deliver different levels of aggro, here is a general guideline from <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>most</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>least</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> aggro:<br>
<br>
Weapons that add raw points of hate(Enraging Blow, Taunting Blow, Warrior Epic)<br>
Weapons that proc a Stun effect (Anarchy, Sanity Warp)<br>
Weapons that proc a Slow effect (Energy Sap, Breath of the Sea)<br>
Weapons that proc a debuff (Frostbite, Venomous Blast)<br>
Weapons that proc Direct Damage or DoT's <br>
<br>
The weapons in the top 2 catagories are really only attainable by members of higher level guilds or the filty rich. It's best to seek out the the best weapons Proc-wise you can get without compromising the underlying baseline of a fast weapon mainhand and a good ratio weapon offhand <br>
<br>
The Ornate Sword of the General is a very good ratio weapon that isn't difficult to attain although it has no proc it might still be better then a weapon with a proc and an inferior ratio, A popular chioce for an offhand is the Frostbringer as it has a good offhand ratio and procs a debuff wich gives decent aggro. There is a fast sword that procs a slow effect called a Wavecrasher, This weapon is much easier to attain then any other fast weapons with a good proc and is often reccomended here on these boards. <br>
<br>
In conclusion try to get the best DPS weapons available to you, but keep in mind that procs are the key to aggro in the raid environment, if you are not a heavy raider they are less important, if you frequently attend raids they become more important. <br>
<br>
Hope this is of some help....<br>
